FBIS4-37181 "drnes117_k_94001" FBIS-NES-94-117 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 IRAQ `Scores' of Government Casualties Claimed in South `Scores' of Government Casualties Claimed in South NC1606182594 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution in Arabic 1430 GMT 16 Jun 94 NC1606182594 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution in Arabic 1430 GMT 16 Jun 94 Arabic BFN [Excerpts] Tyrant Saddam's authorities have declared a state of emergency in the (?west) of al-Nasiriyah Governorate in southern Iraq following an attack by one the Islamic resistance forces mujahidin on the command headquarters of [words indistinct] on 3 June. Scores of officers and men of the tyrant's forces were killed and wounded and [words indistinct]. Reporting this from southern Iraq, our sources said the authorities intensified the presence of their forces in al-Nasiriyah and nearby cities and villages in the marshlands in an attempt to isolate the city center from surrounding areas. The sources added that the authorities imposed a three-day curfew on the city center and main streets where the regime's departments and [word indistinct] and security agencies are located. [passage omitted] The sources said the security and intelligence agencies, the ruling party services, and emergency forces launched an extensive campaign of arrests in which a large number of citizens in al-Nasiriyah and its suburbs were arrested. [passage omitted] In a later report from southern Iraq, our sources affirmed that security conditions in al-Nasiriyah Governorate have worsened. They said residents of that rebellious governorate are defying the regime's measures and that many incidents occurred during which clashes happened between angry citizens and the regime forces resulting in deaths and injuries on both sides. [passage omitted]
